news.title: Andhra Pradesh government to lift ban on 22A lands
news.para: Revenue minister Anagani Satya Prasad said during the previous govt, lands were unlawfully placed under 22A to harass landowners and grab their lands.

news.title: Nagpur civic body recovers Rs 83.6 crore property tax as rebate scheme ends
news.para: The scheme offered a 10% rebate for online transactions and a 5% rebate for offline payments during this period. While it encouraged many taxpayers to clear their dues, a significant number failed to take advantage of the opportunity.

news.title: GMRL seeks settlement with homeowners for metro corridor in Gurugram
news.para: Gurugram Metro Rail Limited (GMRL) officials told TOI on Friday that they want to avoid getting hold of the three plots through the land acquisition process as it would likely delay work on the new corridor.

news.title: District administration identifies five South Goa sites for sand mining
news.para: ​​The report, prepared by the district magistrate, identifies five feasible sand mining regions along the Zuari, based on detailed environmental impact assessment studies conducted by the National Institute of Oceanography (NIO).

news.title: Kolhapur civic body seals 24 flats of tax defaulters
news.para: The building, under the Gandhi Maidan divisional ward office's jurisdiction, had flats whose owners owed between Rs 40,000 and Rs 50,000 each in unpaid property tax despite repeated warnings.

news.title: Centre extends SCB term, revives merger talks with Hyderabad civic body
news.para: This decision, along with a gazette notification issued for 55 other Cantonment boards, allows the SCB to operate without holding elections for an additional year.

news.title: Surat: Three government officers booked for making 486 fake property cards
news.para: The police booked deputy director KP Gamit, superintendent AD Patel, and a data entry operator of the City Survey Superintendent office on the complaint lodged by Azad Ramoliya (47), who owns a factory in Ankleshwar and is also engaged in farming.

news.title: Pune civic body sets February 15 deadline for green initiative rebate on property tax
news.para: Officials from the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) said societies and property owners can submit applications at the local ward offices during working hours.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco razes 2,102 illegal structures
news.para: Under the leadership of Cidco managing director and Vice Chairman Vijay Singhal, the Controller of Unauthorized Constructions department for Navi Mumbai NAINA, led by Suresh Mengade, chief vigilance officer, undertook demolition of illegal constructions.

news.title: Hyderabad: High rises towers face water shortage
news.para: The crisis is particularly severe in the plush gated communities of Cyberabad where groundwater levels, as per official records, has plunged to an alarming 15 metres to 25 metres.

news.title: Kolkata: Police arrest two for duping developer of Rs 79 lakh
news.para: The accused, Subhajt Roy alias Bhombal (35) and Bikram Roy (24), of Nawpara in North 24 Parganas used fake work orders to extract money from the 49-year-old victim from Ritchie Road area, claimed the police.

news.title: UP rural development department achieves 13% of PMAY target in five months
news.para: The department's data updated till Jan 2 shows that so far 9,435 houses against the target of 70,834 houses in 2024-25 have been built. During this period, the department sanctioned 44,294 houses, but only 22,325 identified beneficiaries got registered.

news.title: Gurugram: Illegal construction continues in Aravalis despite restrictions
news.para: Workers are busy laying stones, while tractors laden with boulders from the Aravalis traverse the area. This flurry of illegal activities is underway in several areas even though the land is protected under the Aravali notification, a visit by TOI has revealed.

news.title: Centre reimposes GRAP 3 curbs as air quality worsens in Delhi-NCR
news.para: Delhi's air pollution levels showed an increasing trend and the 24-hour average air quality index (AQI) stood at 371 at 4 pm.

news.title: Brookfield delays sale of London's Citypoint office tower: Source
news.para: Canadian investor Brookfield had been seeking around 500 million pounds ($620 million) for the 36-storey office tower, but bids came in below 400 million pounds, prompting the owner to pause the sales process, the source told Reuters.

news.title: Kolkata: NKDA plans crackdown on residential buildings violating commercial-use rule
news.para: Officials said the authorities had been receiving complaints from different quarters over such rampant use of residential space for commercial purposes, and local residents had been complaining about loud noise and music coming from these houses till late at night.

news.title: Yusen Logistics leases two lakh sq ft warehouse from Macrotech Developers in Palava
news.para: The built-to-suit facility is part of Lodha Industrial & Logistics Parks (LILP) and is strategically chosen to enhance the Tokyo-headquartered company’s distribution network in India.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh govt launches online survey for transparent beneficiary selection in PMAY
news.para: The survey will be facilitated through the recently launched Awas Plus App, designed to ensure transparency in the selection of beneficiaries while simplifying the process of providing housing under the scheme.

news.title: Maharashtra deputy CM directs officials to come up with 'housing for all' policy
news.para: Shinde, who holds the housing and urban development department, also asked officials to clear impediments in the redevelopment of housing projects in Mumbai which have been stuck for various reasons.
